Clone:
=====
* git clone git@github.com:usv299792458/configs.git 1111-configs-git
* cd 1111-configs-git
* <insert here 'Config' section below>
* Edit files in this directory, then stage, then simply 'git push' / 'git pull'

Setup:
=====
* mkdir 1111-configs-git
* cd 1111-configs-git
* git init
* <insert here 'Config' section below>
* <write this content to README>
* git add README
* git commit -m 'first commit'
* git remote add origin git@github.com:usv299792458/configs.git
* git push -u origin master # -u here is needed for 'git pull' to work.
* Edit files in this directory, then stage, then simply 'git push' / 'git pull'

Config:
=====
* git config user.name "Individual User"
* git config user.email usv299792458@gmail.com
* git config core.editor nano
* git config alias.rs 'reset HEAD' # 'git rs file' - unstage a file
* git config --add color.ui true
* git config alias.ci commit
* git config alias.st status
* git config alias.lg 'log -p'
* git config alias.co 'checkout --' # 'git co file' - discard changes in working directory
* git config alias.wdiff 'diff --color-words'
* echo export LESS=R >> ~/.bashrc # enable mouse scroll in pager; drawback: launches pager even on small output
* git config alias.sdiff 'diff --staged'
* git config alias.swdiff 'diff --staged --color-words'
* git config alias.adiff 'diff HEAD'
* git config alias.awdiff 'diff HEAD --color-words'
* git config alias.uc 'reset --soft HEAD^' # undo last commit
